overview: The user initiated a project to enhance a sleep questionnaire
  application by adding database capabilities, an admin dashboard, and an
  authentication system. The initial evaluation identified the need for a
  database schema to store questionnaire responses, API endpoints for data
  interaction, and a client-facing dashboard with secure access. The plan
  involved using NeonDB (PostgreSQL) with Prisma for database management,
  creating dedicated API routes for data operations, and developing a simple
  admin dashboard. A key decision was to implement a streamlined authentication
  system. Initially, a custom session management approach was proposed, but it
  was later simplified to leverage Next.js middleware for route protection and a
  basic cookie-based authentication, which was more efficient for the specified
  single-password admin access. The demographics collected were also updated to
  align with the SOW while retaining useful existing fields. The implementation
  is complete, and the user has been provided with clear instructions for
  database setup and testing.
